Components:

1. ESP32 WROOM 32 Development Board: This is your microcontroller that connects to WiFi and processes the text-to-speech response.


2. PAM8403 Audio Amplifier: This is used to amplify the audio output for your speaker.


3. Speaker: You can use a small phone speaker or an 8Ω speaker to produce sound.


4. Jumper Wires: To make all the necessary connections.


5. 5V Power Source: You can use the ESP32’s 5V pin to power the PAM8403 amplifier.


